# qedge — environment template. Copy to `.env` on the VPS and fill in.
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#   chmod 0600 .env
#
# .env is gitignored (see repo .gitignore: `*.env`). Never commit a real
# password here. This file (.env.example) is the only one that ships in git
# and it must keep an EMPTY placeholder.

# Hysteria2 client auth password.
#   - Generate with: `openssl rand -base64 32` (or `pwgen -s 40 1`).
#   - Use a random string of at least 32 characters; longer is fine.
#   - Rotate when switching profiles (i.e. whenever you stop and re-issue the
#     pre-prepared sing-box client config to either admin). Rotation
#     procedure is in ./README.md.
#   - Treat as a shared secret between the two admins; transport via the
#     mesh / sealed note, not in plaintext mail.
QEDGE_PASSWORD=
